<br>
Well...it's not like I'm all that good to begin with....<br>
<br>
Anyway, my major problem is chliches. They lodge themselves in my brain and won't leave, no matter what i try. Oh, I do all right with them, i suppose. That's really what i don't want. I'd rather be doing a crappy job on an original idea than a stellar or at least half-way-decent one on a cliche one that you can predict by the end of the first paragraph.<br>
<br>
So...Any one out there have any good ways to turn off cliche mode or bust out of my rut?<br>
<br>
